 <body>
  <h1>
   draw_set_font
  </h1>
  This function will set the font to be used for all further text drawing. This font must have been added into the
  <a href="../../../../The_Asset_Editors/Fonts.htm">
   font assets
  </a>
  of the game or have been created using either the
  <a href="../../Asset_Management/Fonts/font_add.htm">
   <span>
    font_add
   </span>
   <span>
    ()
   </span>
   <span>
   </span>
  </a>
  or
  <a href="../../Asset_Management/Fonts/font_add_sprite.htm">
   <span>
    font_add_sprite
   </span>
   <span>
    ()
   </span>
   <span>
   </span>
  </a>
  .
  <h4>
   Syntax:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml">draw_set_font(font);
</code></pre>
  <table>
   <tbody>
    <tr>
     <th>
      Argument
     </th>
     <th>
      Type
     </th>
     <th>
      Description
     </th>
    </tr>
    <tr>
     <td>
      font
     </td>
     <td>
      <span>
       <a href="../../../../../The_Asset_Editors/Fonts.htm">
        Font Asset
       </a>
      </span>
     </td>
     <td>
      The name of the font to use.
     </td>
    </tr>
   </tbody>
  </table>
  <h4>
   Returns:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml">N/A
</code></pre>
  <h4>
   Example:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml">draw_set_colour(c_blue);
draw_set_font(fnt_Game);
draw_text(200, 200, "Hello World");
</code></pre>
  The above code will draw the given text using the font indexed in the variable "fnt_Game" and coloured blue.
 </body>
